LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 1015
Introduced by Ibach, 44; Dorn, 30.
Read first time January 13, 2026
Committee: Business and Labor
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to business innovation; to amend sections
2 81-12,152, 81-12,154, and 81-12,155, Reissue Revised Statutes of
3 Nebraska, and sections 48-602, 48-622.01, 48-648, 48-649.01, and
4 48-657, Revised Statutes Supplement, 2025; to redefine a term and
5 change provisions relating to the combined tax and the state
6 unemployment insurance tax rate under the Employment Security Law;
7 to change provisions relating to legislative findings and qualified
8 action plans and create a fund under the Business Innovation Act; to
9 harmonize provisions; and to repeal the original sections.
10 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
