2 Sec. 6. Section 81-12,152, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
3 amended to read:
4 81-12,152 Sections 81-12,152 to 81-12,166 and section 9 of this act
5 shall be known and may be cited as the Business Innovation Act.
6 Sec. 7. Section 81-12,154, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
7 amended to read:
8 81-12,154 The purpose of the Business Innovation Act is to encourage
9 and support the transfer of Nebraska-based technology and innovation in
10 rural and urban areas of Nebraska in order to create high growth, high
11 technological companies, small businesses, and microenterprises and to
12 enhance creation of wealth and quality jobs. The Legislature finds that
13 the act will:
14 (1) Provide technical assistance planning grants pursuant to section
15 81-12,157 to facilitate phase one applications for the federal grant
16 program;
17 (2) Provide financial assistance pursuant to section 81-12,157 to
18 companies receiving phase one and phase two grants pursuant to the
19 federal grant program;
20 (3) Provide financial assistance pursuant to section 81-12,158 to
21 companies or individuals creating prototypes;
22 (4) Establish a financial assistance program pursuant to section
23 81-12,159 for innovation in value-added agriculture;
24 (5) Establish a financial assistance program for innovation in
25 biosciences;
26 (6) Establish a financial assistance program pursuant to section
27 81-12,160 to identify commercial products and processes;
28 (7) Provide financial assistance pursuant to section 81-12,161 to
29 companies using Nebraska public or private college and university
30 researchers and facilities for applied research projects;
31 (8) Provide support and funding pursuant to section 81-12,162 for
-16-

LB1015 LB1015
2026 2026
1 microlending entities, microenterprise entities, and innovation hubs; and
2 (9) Provide support for locally owned and operated Nebraska-based,
3 high growth businesses by providing technical resources to foster
4 development, growth, and high wage creation. For purposes of this
5 subdivision, Nebraska-based, high growth business means a corporation,
6 partnership, limited liability company, limited partnership, or limited
7 liability partnership registered with the Secretary of State that has two
8 to fifty employees and has annual sales of no less than five hundred
9 thousand dollars and no more than two million five hundred thousand
10 dollars; and .
11 (10) Establish that any entity receiving financial assistance under
12 the Business Innovation Act and that employs any person in this state,
13 whether or not such entity is subject to the Employment Security Law,
14 shall be required to submit to the Department of Labor quarterly wage
15 reports on such forms and in such manner as the Commissioner of Labor may
16 require.
