3 to the Governor for approval.
4 Sec. 9. (1) The Business Innovation Cash Fund is created. The fund
5 shall be used to carry out the Business Innovation Act, except that the
6 fund shall not be used for purposes of sections 81-12,155.01 and
7 81-12,163.01. The fund shall consist of deposits to the fund as required
8 by sections 48-648 and 48-649 to 48-649.04. Any money in the fund
9 available for investment shall be invested by the state investment
10 officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital Expansion Act and the Nebraska
11 State Funds Investment Act.
12 (2) Money in the fund shall be expended by the department for the
13 purpose of:
14 (a) Carrying out the Business Innovation Act, except that such money
15 shall not be expended for the purpose of carrying out the Bioscience
16 Innovation Program; and
17 (b) Payment of unemployment benefits if determined necessary by the
18 Commissioner of Labor.
19 (3) The department, or any entity with which the department
20 contracts for such purpose, may use up to five percent of any
21 appropriation from the fund for administrative expenses.
22 Sec. 10. Original sections 81-12,152, 81-12,154, and 81-12,155,
23 Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, and sections 48-602, 48-622.01,
24 48-648, 48-649.01, and 48-657, Revised Statutes Supplement, 2025, are
25 repealed.
